# Cookbook PR Draft

## Suggested title

LFM Speech Dataset Studio: Bangla Speech Audit, Repair Potential, and Reviewable Action Cards

## Suggested PR category

Community Project

## Suggested description

This PR adds a community project demonstrating a local-first low-resource speech dataset workflow around Liquid models. The project audits LFM-Audio GGUF runner behavior, evaluates a Bangla ASR baseline, measures Liquid text-model transcript repair potential, applies abstaining evidence routing, and generates schema-valid reviewable JSONL action cards.

The project is intentionally claim-safe: it does not report LFM-Audio Bangla ASR quality unless the local runner produces valid transcripts.

## Why it fits

- Demonstrates practical local-first deployment concerns.
- Includes Liquid model usage.
- Provides reproducible logs and artifacts.
- Avoids unsupported model claims.
- Covers safety and review-gating.

## PR checklist

- [ ] Add project link to community examples.
